attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, version 1 (ARM), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a malicious IoT botnet agent, specifically a Mirai variant targeting ARM-based devices. It exhibits characteristic self-propagation and exploitation behaviors, most notably targeting the Huawei TR-064/UPnP DeviceUpgrade vulnerability. Function sub_c51c builds an HTTP POST request containing a command injection payload designed to download and execute further malicious stages (e.g., 'chmod 777 * /tmp/ki; /tmp/ki huawei'). It performs network reconnaissance using SSDP discovery (sub_b0e4) and implements process-scanning logic by traversing /proc to monitor or kill competing processes. The presence of hardcoded credentials ('dslf-config') and fake user-agents further confirms its malicious intent.
